biography: At Firstpost, we focus on facts, keep the noise out and bring you stories from across the globe, viewing them through the Indian lens.

latestIgtvVideos.caption: #VantageOnFirstpost: Bhutan's Prime Minister Tshering Togbay was in India to attend the oath-taking ceremony of Prime Minister Narendra Modi. In an exclusive conversation, @palkisharmaupadhyay asked him about his expectations from PM Modi's third term, the Bhutan-India relationship and how India can boost its neighbourhood first policy. Listen into this conversation.

#FirstpostAfrica: South Africa is at a pivotal point as it gets ready to vote in the general election on May 29. Several polls predict a dwindling support for the African National Congress. With the MK party making some gains and even threatening to pull away voters from opposition parties, analysts say Jacob Zuma could be in a position to be kingmaker. The main opposition party, the Democratic Alliance, has intensified its political campaign, hoping for the fall of the ANC. The DA held its biggest rally in 30 years in Durban to wrest the KwaZulu Natal province from the ANC. Watch our exclusive ground report from the Democratic Alliance "Rescue South Africa Rally" in Durban

#FirstSports: In an exclusive interview with Firstpost, @gukesh.official reflects on his Candidates tournament triumph. Discover the sacrifices made by his parents who helped nurture their son's dreams. Gukesh gets emotional over the response he got India return. He opens up on the heartwarming story of his parents' struggles.. What prepared this young mastermind to gear up for the ultimate chess challenge? @ruphas brings you the exclusive interview.

#FirstSports: On International Women's Day, @mirzasaniar indulges in a candid conversation with Sports Editor @ruphas. The former grand slam champion focuses on her personal life and the how her life transitioned after becoming a mother. From her life decisions to daily routine, Sania's son Izhaan plays a pivotal role in decision making. But there is one thing that connects the mother-son duo. Izhaan has a soft spot for Al-Nassr star Cristiano Ronaldo. Rupha Ramani in conversation with Sania Mirza.

#FirstSports: On International Women's Day, @mirzasaniar gave out a strong statement about women empowerment. The Tennis icon not only highlighted her personal issues but also opened up on what makes her anxious. In an exclusive interview with @ruphas, Sania highlighted the societal norms about marriage and how some of them needs to change. From focusing on on her career to life after retirement, Sania and Rupha indulge in a candid conversation. Sania also has a word of advice for the women around the globe.

#FirstpostDefenceSummit: Ukraine's Senior Diplomat Dr Olexander Scherba discussed the impact of Artificial Intelligence in modern day warfare at Firstpost Defence Summit 2024. Scherba said Ukraine has been able to fight Russia with the help of AI and tech. Listen into this exclusive conversation.

#FirstpostDefenceSummit: At the Firstpost Defence Summit 2024, global leaders discuss the importance of India's global defence partnerships. New Delhi's push for diversification in the defence sector is an ambitious task. How can India achieve this milestone? What are the challenges ahead of the government and the military forces? In this session of the summit, leaders disseminate how India can achieve this goal while navigating the roadmap of diversification in defence.

#FirstpostDefenceSummit: Rear Admiral Rahul Kumar Shrawat (Retd.), Chairman and Managing Director of Naval Group India Pvt Ltd, discusses India's self-reliance in defense at the Firstpost Defence Summit 2024. Rear Admiral Shrawat hailed the Indian Navy for being at the forefront of self-reliance through indigenization. Talking about the importance of building submarines in India, Rear Admiral Shrawat praises the government's decision to build more Scorpene submarines in the country.

Amid Israel-Hamas and Russia-Ukraine wars, Minister of State for External Affairs @mrs.mlekhi  said that defence is a relevant topic of discussion with so much happening around the world and that the purpose of defence diplomacy should not be to enter into wars but to end wars.

Speaking at the ‘Firspost Defence Summit 2024’, Lekhi said, “Considering all that is happening around us, it’s one of the areas where we all need to engage in. We have been engaging over a long period of time but we still need to engage in more because purpose of defence diplomacy is really not to enter into wars but to end wars."

#FirstpostAmerica | US: Diet Coke Fan Trump Says Coca-Cola to Ditch Corn Syrup For Cane Sugar 

US President Donald Trump claimed on Truth Social that Coca-Cola has agreed to switch from high-fructose corn syrup to real cane sugar in American products. While Coca-Cola acknowledged the President's enthusiasm, the company did not confirm any deal. Most US variants currently use corn syrup, unlike those in India or the UK. The announcement comes amid the White House's new "Make America Healthy Again" campaign targeting processed ingredients.

#FirstpostAmerica | US: Trump Hosts Bahrain, Qatar Leaders as Syria, Gaza Crises Intensify

President Donald Trump held high-level meetings with Bahrain's Crown Prince Salman bin Hamad Al-Khalifa and Qatar's Prime Minister Mohammed bin Abdulrahman Al Thani, as tensions rise across the Middle East. Bahrain pledged over $17 billion in US investments, including a major deal with Boeing and a new civil nuclear agreement. Trump's talks with the Qatari PM focused on Gaza ceasefire negotiations and regional security. These meetings come as Israeli airstrikes target Damascus and Druze-Bedouin clashes escalate in Syria's Sweida province. US Secretary of State Marco Rubio announced steps to help stabilise the region.

#FirstpostAmerica: "She Took Me Back": Barack Obama on Divorce Rumours 

Barack and Michelle Obama have addressed persistent divorce rumours for the first time in a new episode of Michelle's podcast IMO, co-hosted with her brother Craig Robinson. The former US President made a rare appearance, bringing humour and clarity to recent speculation about their marriage. The rumours had intensified earlier this year when Michelle skipped former President Jimmy Carter's funeral and Donald Trump's second inauguration.

#FirstpostAmerica: Are There No Beggars in Cuba?

A senior Cuban minister has resigned after claiming that there are no beggars in Cuba, sparking national outrage. During a televised parliamentary session, the official said people seen rummaging through rubbish were "disguised as beggars" trying to make "easy money." Her comments were met with fierce backlash online, with citizens sharing images of poverty and comparing her to Marie Antoinette.

#FirstpostAmerica: Loro Piana Sweatshops: Luxury Abusing Labour 

Luxury cashmere brand Loro Piana has been placed under court supervision for a year after an Italian investigation uncovered labour abuses in its supply chain. A Chinese tailor working 13-hour days in a Milan sweatshop triggered the probe after alleging assault and unpaid wages. Authorities found undocumented workers toiling 90-hour weeks for less than $5/hour in unsafe conditions.
